DataElement.preferredName: Experiment 2-Dimensional Liquid Chromatography First Dimension Protocol Identifier java.lang.Long
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A set of actions and observations, performed to verify or falsify a hypothesis or research a causal relationship between phenomena.:The property of being measured and described using two orthogonal directions.:A type of chromatography in which separation of a mixture is achieved by passing a sample in a stream of liquid solvent through some form of material that will provide resistance by virtue of chemical interactions between the components of the sample and the material.:Preceding all others in time or space or degree.:The magnitude of something in a particular direction, especially length or width or height.:A rule which guides how an activity should be performed._One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is a long integer (64-bit two's complement).
